    "summary": "This technical paper provides a rigorous critique of the Observer Patch Holography (OPH) framework, identifying a fundamental structural tension between its axiomatic foundations and its mathematical implementation. While OPH assumes finite-dimensional observer patches, it relies on Tomita–Takesaki modular theory—a formalism that yields non-trivial dynamics only within the infinite degrees of freedom characteristic of Type III von Neumann algebras. Key Contributions: Algebraic Discontinuity: We demonstrate that in a finite (Type I) Hilbert space, the modular operator produces only trivial unitary transformations, failing to account for the Unruh effect and Hawking radiation without an explicit continuum limit (N→∞). UEET Resolution: We propose the Unified Energy Exchange Theory (UEET) as t"
